hwVoiceDialControlMIB.name: hwVoiceDialControlMIB
hwVoiceDialControlMIB.contactinfo: PLAT Team Huawei 3Com Technologies co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085

hwVoPeerCommonConfigTable.name: hwVoPeerCommonConfigTable
hwVoPeerCommonConfigTable.description: The table contains the voice peer common information .

hwVoPeerCommonConfigEntry.name: hwVoPeerCommonConfigEntry
hwVoPeerCommonConfigEntry.description: The common informatioin of voice peer.

hwVoPeerConfigIndex.name: hwVoPeerConfigIndex
hwVoPeerConfigIndex.description: Index of voice peer common table. It identify the number of the voice peer.

hwVoPeerConfigType.name: hwVoPeerConfigType
hwVoPeerConfigType.description: Specify the type of voice peer.

hwVoPeerConfigDesPattern.name: hwVoPeerConfigDesPattern
hwVoPeerConfigDesPattern.description: The number associated with this voice peer.Character include '0' to '9','*','#','+','.','T' can be configured in this number.

hwVoPeerConfigCodec1st.name: hwVoPeerConfigCodec1st
hwVoPeerConfigCodec1st.description: This object expresses the first desirable codec of speech for the peer.

hwVoPeerConfigCodec2st.name: hwVoPeerConfigCodec2st
hwVoPeerConfigCodec2st.description: This object expresses the second desirable codec of speech for the peer.

hwVoPeerConfigCodec3st.name: hwVoPeerConfigCodec3st
hwVoPeerConfigCodec3st.description: This object expresses the third desirable codec of speech for the peer.

hwVoPeerConfigCodec4st.name: hwVoPeerConfigCodec4st
hwVoPeerConfigCodec4st.description: This object expresses the forth desirable codec with of speech for the peer.

hwVoPeerConfigIpPreced.name: hwVoPeerConfigIpPreced
hwVoPeerConfigIpPreced.description: This object expresses the ip precedence of voice packets. The default value is 0.

hwVoPeerConfigShutDown.name: hwVoPeerConfigShutDown
hwVoPeerConfigShutDown.description: This object expresses the current status of the peer.

hwVoPeerConfigVADSwitch.name: hwVoPeerConfigVADSwitch
hwVoPeerConfigVADSwitch.description: Enable or disable the VAD (Voice Activity Detection).

hwVoPeerConfigDtmfRelay.name: hwVoPeerConfigDtmfRelay
hwVoPeerConfigDtmfRelay.description: set the DTMF relay type in this dial-peer.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxLevel.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxLevel
hwVoPeerConfigFaxLevel.description: This object expresses the fax level in this dial-peer.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxRate.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxRate
hwVoPeerConfigFaxRate.description: This object expresses the fax transmit rate.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxLocalTrainParam.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxLocalTrainParam
hwVoPeerConfigFaxLocalTrainParam.description: This object expresses the fax local train threshold in this dial-peer. The default value is 10.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxProtocol.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxProtocol
hwVoPeerConfigFaxProtocol.description: This object expresses the fax protocol which this dial-peer support. The default value is t38.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38HighRedunPackNumber.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38HighRedunPackNumber
hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38HighRedunPackNumber.description: This object expresses the high speed redundancy packet numbers when t38 fax protocol is used for this dial-peer .

hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38LowRedunPackNumber.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38LowRedunPackNumber
hwVoPeerConfigFaxT38LowRedunPackNumber.description: This object expresses the low speed redundancy packet numbers when t38 fax protocol is used for this dial-peer .

hwVoPeerConfigFaxSendNSFSwitch.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxSendNSFSwitch
hwVoPeerConfigFaxSendNSFSwitch.description: This object expresses whether or not send nsf to fax in this dial-peer.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxSupportMode.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxSupportMode
hwVoPeerConfigFaxSupportMode.description: This object expresses the fax support mode in this dial-peer.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxTrainMode.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxTrainMode
hwVoPeerConfigFaxTrainMode.description: This object expresses the fax train mode in this dial-peer.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxRelay.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxRelay
hwVoPeerConfigFaxRelay.description: This object expresses ecm mode is used in fax transmit or not.

hwVoPeerConfigRowStatus.name: hwVoPeerConfigRowStatus
hwVoPeerConfigRowStatus.description: This object specifies the status of this conceptual row, which is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

hwVoPeerConfigFaxPassthroughMode.name: hwVoPeerConfigFaxPassthroughMode
hwVoPeerConfigFaxPassthroughMode.description: set pcm fax protocol passthrough mode It is valid only when fax protocol is pcm .

hwVoPeerConfigPriority.name: hwVoPeerConfigPriority
hwVoPeerConfigPriority.description: This object specifies the priority of this voice entity. It is between 0 and 10. The highest priority is 0, the lowest priority is 10, and 0 is the default value.

hwVoPeerConfigAuthorizationLevel.name: hwVoPeerConfigAuthorizationLevel
hwVoPeerConfigAuthorizationLevel.description: This object specifies the caller level for local authorization. The level is between 0 and 9. The highest level is 9, the lowest level is 0, and 0 is the default value.

hwVoPeerConfigDescription.name: hwVoPeerConfigDescription
hwVoPeerConfigDescription.description: This object specifies the textual description of this voice entity.

hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberType.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberType
hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberType.description: This object specifies the numbering type of calling number about this voice entity. abbreviated - the numbering type is abbreviated. international - the numbering type is international. national - the numbering type is national. network - the numbering type is network. reserved - the numbering type is reserved. subscriber - the numbering type is subscriber. unknown - the numbering type is unkown.

hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberType.name: hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberType
hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberType.description: This object specifies the numbering type of called number about this voice entity. abbreviated - the numbering type is abbreviated. international - the numbering type is international. national - the numbering type is national. network - the numbering type is network. reserved - the numbering type is reserved. subscriber - the numbering type is subscriber. unknown - the numbering type is unkown.

hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberingPlan.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberingPlan
hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumberingPlan.description: This object specifies the numbering plan of calling number about this voice entity. data - data numbering plan. isdn - ISDN/telephone numbering plan. national - national standard numbering plan. private - Private numbering plan. reserved - Reserved for extension. telex - telex numbering plan. unknown - unknown.

hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberingPlan.name: hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberingPlan
hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumberingPlan.description: This object specifies the numbering plan of called number about this voice entity. data - data numbering plan. isdn - ISDN/telephone numbering plan. national - national standard numbering plan. private - Private numbering plan. reserved - Reserved for extension. telex - telex numbering plan. unknown - unknown.

hwVoPeerConfigSelectStop.name: hwVoPeerConfigSelectStop
hwVoPeerConfigSelectStop.description: This object specifies no further entity searching allowed if a call started on the this voice entity.

hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumSubstRule.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumSubstRule
hwVoPeerConfigCallingNumSubstRule.description: This object specifies number-substitute rule that apply calling number of this voice entity. It is valid if its value is between 1 and 2147483647. This voice entity doesn't apply any number-substitute rule if its value is 0.

hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumSubstRule.name: hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumSubstRule
hwVoPeerConfigCalledNumSubstRule.description: This object specifies number-substitute rule that apply called number of this voice entity. It is valid if its value is between 1 and 2147483647. This voice entity doesn't apply any number-substitute rule if its value is 0.

hwVoPeerConfigMaxCall.name: hwVoPeerConfigMaxCall
hwVoPeerConfigMaxCall.description: The object specifies that this voice entity is bound with a tag that indicates a maximum call value. The value of 0 specifies that cancel the act of binding.

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigTable.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigTable
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigTable.description: The table contains the pots peer information .

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigIndex.description: Index of voice pots peer table. It identify the number of the voice pots peer.

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigCancelTruncateEnable.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigCancelTruncateEnable
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigCancelTruncateEnable.description: Cancel truncate the called number in this dial-peer.

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPrefix.description: This object expresses the pattern to be added before the dialed number. Valid character include '0' to '9' and ','.

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPort.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPort
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigPort.description: set the voice port and group associated with this peer.The port number is seperated with group number by ':'.As analog voice port,the group number can be represented by 255.

hwVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNumber.name: hwVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNumber
hwVoPOTSPeerConfigSendNumber.description: This object specifies the number digits to send to the destination. It can take the value: 0-31 number of right-justified digits of the match-template to be sent. -1 Truncate the called number(default). -2 send all match-template digits.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTable.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTable
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTable.description: The table contains the voip peer information.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigIndex.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigIndex
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigIndex.description: Index of voice voip peer table. It identify the number of the voip voice peer.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTargetType.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTargetType
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTargetType.description: This object expresses the type of the session target for this peer .

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTarget.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTarget
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSessionTarget.description: This object expresses the ip address IPV4 peer.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigFastSwitch.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigFastSwitch
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigFastSwitch.description: This object expresses whether or not the fast connect function enable.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTunnelSwitch.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTunnelSwitch
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTunnelSwitch.description: This object expresses whether or not the tunnel function enable. It cannot be used when no fast connect .

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTeachPrefix.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTeachPrefix
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigTeachPrefix.description: This object expresses the technology prefix. Valid charater include '0' to '9', '#'.

hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSendRing.name: hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSendRing
hwVoVoIPPeerConfigSendRing.description: enable/disable the send ring. It is valid only when fast connect is enabled .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigCancelTrun.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigCancelTrun
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigCancelTrun.description: The default value of dial peer's Cancel trun

hwVoPeerDefaultConfig1STCodecLevel.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfig1STCodecLevel
hwVoPeerDefaultConfig1STCodecLevel.description: The default value of voice entity 1st codec level priority g711alaw G.711 A Law 64000 bps g711ulaw G.711 U Law 64000 bps g723r53 G.723.1 5300 bps g723r63 G.723.1 6300 bps g729r8 G.729 8000 bps g729a G.729 A

hwVoPeerDefaultConfig2NDCodecLevel.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfig2NDCodecLevel
hwVoPeerDefaultConfig2NDCodecLevel.description: The default value of voice entity 2nd codec level priority g711alaw G.711 A Law 64000 bps g711ulaw G.711 U Law 64000 bps g723r53 G.723.1 5300 bps g723r63 G.723.1 6300 bps g729r8 G.729 8000 bps g729a G.729 A

hwVoPeerDefaultConfig3RDCodecLevel.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfig3RDCodecLevel
hwVoPeerDefaultConfig3RDCodecLevel.description: The default value of voice entity 3rd codec level priority g711alaw G.711 A Law 64000 bps g711ulaw G.711 U Law 64000 bps g723r53 G.723.1 5300 bps g723r63 G.723.1 6300 bps g729r8 G.729 8000 bps g729a G.729 A

hwVoPeerDefaultConfig4THCodecLevel.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfig4THCodecLevel
hwVoPeerDefaultConfig4THCodecLevel.description: The default value of voice entity 4th codec level priority g711alaw G.711 A Law 64000 bps g711ulaw G.711 U Law 64000 bps g723r53 G.723.1 5300 bps g723r63 G.723.1 6300 bps g729r8 G.729 8000 bps g729a G.729 A

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigVADOn.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigVADOn
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigVADOn.description: The default value of dial peer's VAD Switch

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTransmitLevel.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTransmitLevel
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTransmitLevel.description: The default value of dial peer's FaxTransmitLevel.The unit is db

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLocalTrain.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLocalTrain
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLocalTrain.description: The default value of dial peer's Fax local train threshold .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxProtocol.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxProtocol
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxProtocol.description: The default value of dial peer's Fax Protocol .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxHSRedundancy.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxHSRedundancy
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxHSRedundancy.description: The default value of dial peer's T38 Fax Protocol High Redundancy.

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLSRedundancy.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLSRedundancy
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxLSRedundancy.description: The default value of dial peer's T38 Fax Protocol Low Redundancy.

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxBaudrate.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxBaudrate
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxBaudrate.description: The default value of dial peer's Fax Baudrate .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxNSF.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxNSF
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxNSF.description: The default value of fax non-standard faculty .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxSupportMode.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxSupportMode
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxSupportMode.description: The default value of fax SupportMode .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTrainMode.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTrainMode
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxTrainMode.description: The default value of fax TrainMode .

hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxECM.name: hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxECM
hwVoPeerDefaultConfigFaxECM.description: The default value of fax ECM Mode .

hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumTable.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumTable
hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumTable.description: The table contains caller number permitted information in the specific voice entity for incoming call.

hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumEntry.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumEntry
hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumEntry.description: A single caller number permitted in the specific voice entity for incoming call. The entry is created when its associated voPeerCommonCfgEntry is created. This entry is deleted when its associated voPeerCommonCfgEntry is deleted.

hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNum.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNum
hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNum.description: This object specifies caller number permitted that must be of the form ^(([0-9ABCD#*.!+%[]()\-]+(\$)!)|(\$))$. Specially set this object $ meaning allow caller null.

hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumRowStatus.name: hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumRowStatus
hwVoPeerConfigCallerPermitNumRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.
